\b\fs28 D. Command Prompt\par
\b0\fs20\par
You can run Halo from a Windows command prompt (e.g., C:\\Program Files\\Microsoft Games\\Halo\\Halo.exe). The following is a list of arguments you may use running Halo from a command prompt entering \ldblquote halo.exe \endash\i argument\i0 .\rdblquote\par
\par
\b -?\par
\b0 Displays a list of all arguments.\par
\par
\b -nosound\par
\b0 Disables all sound.\par
\par
\b -novideo\par
\b0 Disables video playback.\par
\par
\b -nojoystick \par
\b0 Disables joystick/gamepads.\par
\par
\b -nogamma\par
\b0 Disables adjustment of gamma.\par
\par
\b -useff\par
\b0 Forces the game to run as a fixed function card.\par
\par
\b -use11\par
\b0 Forces the game to run as a shader 1.1 card.\par
\par
\b -use20\par
\b0 Forces the game to run as a shader 2.0 card.\par
\par
\b -safemode\par
\b0 Disables as much as possible from the game.\par
\par
\b -window\par
\b0 Runs the game in a window.\par
\par
\b -width640\par
\b0 Forces the game to run at 640x480.\par
\par
\b -vidmode w,h,r \par
\b0 Forces the game to run at width, height, refresh rate.\par
\par
\b -adapter \i x\i0\par
\b0 Forces the game to run fullscreen on a multimon adaptor.\par
\par
\b -port \i x\i0\par
\b0 Server port address used when hosting games.\par
\par
\b -cport \i x\i0\par
\b0 Client port address used when joining games.\par
\par
\b -ip \i x.x.x.x\i0\par
\b0 Server IP address used when you have multiple IP addresses.\par
\par
\b -screenshot\par
\b0 Enables the "Print Screen" key to generate screenshots\par
\par
\b -timedemo\par
\b0 Runs four movies and writes out timedemo.txt.\par
\par
\b -console\par
\b0 Enables the debugging console.\par
\par
\b Notes:\b0  \par
\pard\nowidctlpar\fi-360\li720\tx720\f5\'a7\tab\f0 A number of these command prompt arguments are used by PSS to troubleshoot problems.\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\fi-360\li720\f5\'a7\tab\f0 Many of the command prompt arguments mirror functionality available from within the standard Halo user interface.\par
