\b\fs28 E. Configuration Issues\par
\b0\fs20\par
Known hardware and operating system configuration issues are listed in this section. For issues with specific 3D cards, see section F, "3D Card Issues."\par
\par
For assistance with top performance issues, visit http://support.microsoft.com/?pr=gmsperf.\par
\b\par
Performance may be poor after standby or suspend mode:\b0  If you manually or automatically put your computer on standby or suspend mode while playing the game, performance may be poor when you come out of standby or suspend mode and resume the game: music and sounds may not be heard, transitions may be choppy, or the game may hang. To resolve, restart the game.\par
\par
\b Enable direct memory access (DMA) in your IDE controller on Windows 98 Second Edition and Windows Millennium Edition: \b0 When you enable DMA on your computer, you improve the game performance and stability. \par
\par
\pard To enable DMA: \par
\pard\fi-360\li492\ri360\sb100\sa1\sl288\slmult1\tx720 1.\tab Close all programs that are running on your computer. \par
\pard\fi-360\li492\ri360\sb100\sa1\sl288\slmult1 2.\tab Click \b Start\b0 , point to \b Settings\b0 , and then click \b Control Panel\b0 . \par
3.\tab Double-click \b System\b0 . \par
4.\tab Click the \b Device Manager\b0  tab. \par
5.\tab Click the PLUS SIGN \b (+)\b0  next to \b Disk Drives\b0 . \par
6.\tab Click \b IDE/Disk (hard drive)\b0 , and then click \b Properties\b0 . \par
7.\tab On the \b Settings\b0  tab, select \b DMA\b0 . \par
8.\tab Click \b OK\b0 , and then click \b OK\b0  again. \par
9.\tab Restart the computer.\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\b\par
NOTE\b0 : When you enable DMA, you increase the access speed to the CD-ROM drive and the hard disk. Some drivers do not support DMA access. If the DMA check box remains selected after you restart your computer, DMA access is supported.\par
\par
\b Run in server mode, rather than workstation mode in Windows 98 Second Edition and Widows Millennium Edition:\b0  When you enable server mode, you improve game performance.\par
\pard\par
To run in server mode: \par
\pard\fi-360\li490\ri360\sb100\sa1\sl288\slmult1\tx720 1.\tab Right-click on \b My Computer\b0  and select \b Properties\b0 . \par
\pard\fi-360\li490\ri360\sb100\sa1\sl288\slmult1 2.\tab Click the \b Performance\b0  tab. \par
3.\tab Click \b File System\b0 . \par
4.\tab Select \b Network Server\b0  as the typical role of the PC. \par
\pard\sl288\slmult1\b\par
\pard\ri360\sb100\sa1\sl288\slmult1 Make sure that your speaker mode is set to match the type of speaker output on your computer:\b0  This situation might occur if you switch back and forth from listening to headphones and listening to 4.1/5.1 speakers.  Having the incorrect speaker mode set will cause 3D sounds to be heard incorrectly or not at all.\par
To set your speaker mode:\par
\pard\fi-576\li576\ri360\sb100\sa1\sl288\slmult1 1.\tab Click \b Start\b0 , point to \b Settings\b0 , and then click \b Control Panel\b0 .  \par
2.\tab Click on \b Sounds and Multimedia\b0  (Windows 98/Me) or \b Sounds and Audio Devices\b0  (Windows 2000/XP).\par
3.\tab Under \b Speaker settings\b0 , click on the \b Advanced\b0 .\par
4.\tab Select the speaker setup that matches your current speaker setup.\par
5.\tab Click \b OK\b0 , and then click \b OK\b0  again.\par
\pard\ri360\sb100\sa1\sl288\slmult1 If your sound card also came with its own software for setting speaker settings, ensure that these settings are also correct.\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\highlight3\b\par
\highlight0\fs28 F. 3D Card Issues\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\tx0\tx720\b0\fs20\par
Halo only supports DirectX 9.0b-compliant video cards. It is good practice to always install the latest certified drivers for all of your hardware.\par
\par
For assistance with top video issues, visit http://support.microsoft.com/?pr=gmsvideo.\par
\b\par
ATI Radeon 9800 PRO 128:\b0  You may experience inconsistent graphic performance with textures if you set the Mipmap Detail Level in the ATI Direct3D Control Panel to any setting except High Quality.\par
\par
\b NVIDIA Video Cards and FSAA Modes:\b0  You may experience difficulties running Halo using NVIDIA video cards in any of the FSAA modes. If you are having a problem, you should disable the FSAA mode for the NVIDIA video card.\par
\par
\b Via Motherboard Chipsets:\b0  If you have a Via brand motherboard, you may need to update to the latest \ldblquote 4-in-1\rdblquote  motherboard chipset drivers to avoid crashes. \par
\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\tx360\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\b\fs28 G. 3D Card Drivers and Manufacturers\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\tx360\tx720\b0\fs20\par
Make sure that you have the latest drivers from the manufacturer of your video card. Many video issues will be resolved if you install your video card's latest drivers. Halo\i  \i0 may not properly detect some older video cards because their video drivers are not DirectX 9.0b\f1 -\f0 compliant. Contact your video card manufacturer for updated drivers, or install the latest reference drivers for your video board. Note that many reference drivers are not supported by the chipset manufacturer. Listed below are some common video card manufacturers' Web sites.\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\b\par
NOTE: \b0 Use Windows Update (http://windowsupdate.microsoft.com/) to ensure that you are using the latest drivers and have the latest updates to your operating system.\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\tx360\tx720\par
For specific video card drivers, visit the manufacturer\rquote s web site.\par
\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\b\fs28 H. Audio Troubleshooting\par
\cf2\b0\fs20\par
Check with your sound card manufacturer for the latest DirectX-compatible drivers.\par
\par
Following are the known audio issues and workarounds:\par
\cf0\b\par
Users running Windows 98Second Edition and Windows Me:\b0  You should run Windows Update to ensure that you have downloaded all critical updates as well as all the \i recommended\i0  updates. Otherwise, you may have sound problems such as the weapon volume shifting in and out. \par
\pard\nowidctlpar\tx360\b\par
\pard\tx360 Aureal Vortex:\b0  The audio may not function with Aureal sound cards.\~To resolve this issue, turn off the hardware acceleration. From the Start menu, point to \b Settings\b0 , and then choose \b Control Panel\b0 . Double-click \b Sounds and Audio Devices\b0  and select the \b Audio\b0  tab. Click the \b Advanced\b0  button in the Sound Playback section and then click the \b Performance\b0  tab. Move the Hardware Acceleration slider to None and click \b Apply\b0 . \par
\pard\nowidctlpar\b\par
Hercules Game Theater XP sound card in Windows 98Second Edition:\b0  Stuttering and sound distortion may occur using the\b  \b0 Hercules Game Theater XP sound card and Windows 98 Second Edition. See \ldblquote Enable direct memory access (DMA) in your IDE controller on Windows 98 Second Edition\rdblquote  in section E, \ldblquote Configuration Issues.\rdblquote  \par
\pard\nowidctlpar\tx360\b\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\tx360\tx720 Hercules Game Theater XP sound card in Windows XP Professional:\b0  The audio may not function correctly at all times with the Hercules Game Theater XP sounds card. For example, grenade sound effects may play too low. You should make sure you have installed the latest \cf2 DirectX-compatible drivers for your sound card\cf0 .\par
\par
\b Realtek ALC650 sound card in Windows XP Home:\b0  Halo may not function correctly using the Realtek ALC650 sound card in Windows XP if you enable EAX sound in the game. \par
\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\b Montego II Quadzilla sound card in Windows 2000: \b0 The audio may not function correctly at all times with the Montego II Quadzilla sound card. You should make sure you have installed the Montego II Quadzilla Windows NT 4.0 drivers. Information on installing the drivers is available from http://turtlebeach.com.\par
